  "ingredientsTitle": "Ingredients",
  "ingredientGroups": [
   {
    "title": null,
    "items": [
     "6 to 8 chops",
     "100 ml vinegar",
     "80 ml Worcestershire sauce",
     "60ml olive oil",
     "Ina Paarman's rosemary and olive sprinkle"
    ]
   }
  ],
  "directionsTitle": "Method",
  "directionGroups": [
   {
    "title": null,
    "steps": [
     "Mix the vinegar and Worcestershire sauce and marinate the chops in it for about 1 hour.<img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-3-044.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt title=\"MARINDA-BLOG-3-044\">",
     "Set the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.",
     "Pour the olive oil into the bottom of an oven dish and pack the sliced onions on the olive oil, then put the rosemary sprigs on the onions.<img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-3-042.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt title=\"MARINDA-BLOG-3-042\">",
     "Pack the chops on the oil and pour the marinade over the meat.",
     "Sprinkle with the Ina Paarman seasoning &#8211; generously.<img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-3-047.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt title=\"MARINDA-BLOG-3-047\">",
     "It takes about 30 minutes to cook through nicely. After 15 minutes, turn the meat over.<img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-3-056.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt title=\"MARINDA-BLOG-3-056\">",
     "If it's not brown enough, switch on the grill element and grill quickly &#8211; it burns easily so you must keep an eye on the meat."
    ]
   }
  ],
  "notesTitle": "Notes",
  "notes": [
   "Serve these gorgeous browned beauties with any side of your choice. We had ours with potatoes in their jackets and pumpkin. The onions roast up beautifully alongside them. Finger-licking good."
  ],
